The paper focuses on detecting and localizing image forgery in facial images using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and semantic segmentation networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper deals with image forensics and security, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed method also involves loss functions and optimization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
